President Obama has nominated four individuals to serve on the United States District Courts. The nominees are Judge Madeline Cox Arleo for the District of New Jersey, Judge Amos L. Mazzant, III for the Eastern District of Texas, Robert Lee Pitman for the Western District of Texas, and Robert William Schroeder III for the Eastern District of Texas. These nominees have demonstrated a strong commitment to justice and integrity throughout their careers. Their records of public service are impressive, and President Obama is confident that they will serve the American people well from the District Court bench.